Cell[TextData[{
 "For general rational numbers the coefficients ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["a", "j"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "33aa3a6a-db8a-4564-9409-2d51014c86e9"],
 " exhibit eventual periodicity, as shown in the example above. Hence, \
formally we can use the geometric series summation to represent it.  A \
rational number\[CloseCurlyQuote]s p-adic expansion is always eventually \
periodic."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.883596984713049*^9, {3.883597104260064*^9, 3.8835971066853647`*^9}, {
