  3.973814812254957*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1884da0b-a852-4e66-9f37-\
3c2639c411b4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "a rational number in the interval ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", "0"}]}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"235c7a17-ad39-420a-b18b-4d72e43d9e85"],
 " with a periodicity of length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["k", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a4d25fb3-b2ac-422d-8849-bafa032d2890"],
 ">0. The difference between purely and eventually periodic is that in the \
later case we have a non-repeating beginning part"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.883596984713049*^9, {3.883597104260064*^9, 3.8835971066853647`*^9}, {
   3.883597200822399*^9, 3.883597259278998*^9}, {3.883598585469923*^9, 
