Cell["\<\
Now that we can faithfully represent any rational number in \:211a\:209a and \
display it in p-adic Hensel notation, the natural question is: can we compute \
directly with these representations? Addition, multiplication, and inversion \
should all produce exact p-adic rationals \[LongDash] and they do.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.98174369248599*^9, {3.981906232884206*^9, 
   3.981906234723662*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1ce5223f-2dc9-4c4e-8692-\
3afe7c585ce5"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

