Cell["\<\
Notice the period of 3/11 + 2/17 in \:211a\:2085: it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s 80 \
digits long, even though 3/11 has period 5 and 2/17 has period 16. This isn\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t a bug \[LongDash] it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a fundamental \
feature. The period of a sum is bounded by lcm(k\:2081, k\:2082) = lcm(5, 16) \
= 80, because the resulting denominator 187 = 11 \[Times] 17 has \
MultiplicativeOrder[5, 187] = 80. Two rationals with modest periods can \
produce a result whose period is the full product of the original periods. \
This is the p-adic analogue of adding 1/7 + 1/13 in decimal: both have short \
repeating blocks, but 1/91 repeats with period 6 = lcm(6, 6) \[LongDash] or \
worse, when the denominators are coprime and the orders \
don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t share factors, the period can be as large as (d\:2081 \
\[Minus] 1)(d\:2082 \[Minus] 1). The exact representation handles this \
transparently.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9817437427285633`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"c1a516ae-f022-4eea-a8f7-\
c3946d9e764a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Rational Reconstruction from Truncated (lossy) P-adic Expansions\
\>", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.884272873721366*^9, 3.884272950001244*^9}, {
  3.8847071962998953`*^9, 3.884707205688294*^9}, {3.884818916550745*^9, 
  3.8848189474068613`*^9}, {3.981741263185463*^9, 3.98174127546141*^9}, {
  3.981742035015892*^9, 3.981742056418529*^9}, {3.9817433398345003`*^9, 
  3.981743343539362*^9}, {3.981754305610297*^9, 3.9817543059777527`*^9}, {
  3.981755278710973*^9, 
  3.981755281852243*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0b60f336-18b0-4b4e-a880-\
6e3228f518ee"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Recall that ",
 StyleBox["PadicRational[m, p, e, N, k] ", "CodeText"],
 "stores a rational exactly using the significand m \[LongDash] the combined \
digit string \[LongDash] with period k explicit. If k is lost, we retain only \
m and the modulus p\:1d3a, with no record of where repetition begins.\n\n",
 StyleBox["PadicRational /: PadicN[PadicRational[m_,p_,e_,N_,k_]] := \
PadicRationalN[m,p,e,N]", "CodeText"],
 "\n\nAt first glance this seems fatal \[LongDash] periodicity is precisely \
what distinguishes a rational from an arbitrary p-adic integer. But consider \
what m actually encodes: a rational number u/v (numerator u, denominator v) \
satisfies u \[CenterDot] v\:207b\.b9 \[Congruent] m (mod p\:1d3a) \[LongDash] \
meaning m is the residue of u/v in modular arithmetic. \
Wang\[CloseCurlyQuote]s [1981] key insight is that if both |u| and |v| are \
small relative to p\:1d3a \[LongDash] specifically |u|, |v| < ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"p\:1d3a", "/", "2"}], ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b7c20c09-4993-4bc5-ba01-e83d17dbbe47"],
 " \[LongDash] then m uniquely determines u/v, no period needed.\n\nTo make \
this concrete with p = 3, N = 2 (so modulus p\:1d3a = 9):"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.884780948286735*^9, 3.884781115940824*^9}, {
   3.884783202719536*^9, 3.884783294816025*^9}, {3.88478333522262*^9, 
   3.884783400451723*^9}, {3.884783433869664*^9, 3.8847834843046513`*^9}, {
   3.884792054166067*^9, 3.884792072310113*^9}, {3.884793328792128*^9, 
   3.884793332066718*^9}, {3.884793416705949*^9, 3.884793419457988*^9}, {
   3.8848685159186497`*^9, 3.8848685286224117`*^9}, {3.884868616128468*^9, 
   3.884868655406876*^9}, {3.981499516671311*^9, 3.9814995175181627`*^9}, {
   3.981754998098262*^9, 3.981755025943715*^9}, {3.9817550702162046`*^9, 
   3.9817550883173723`*^9}, {3.981755168026005*^9, 3.9817551815186443`*^9}, 
   3.981755310041709*^9, 3.9817553444678698`*^9, {3.98175540373662*^9, 
   3.981755404232251*^9}, {3.981755592051322*^9, 3.981755609939746*^9}, {
   3.981755642195359*^9, 3.98175565107999*^9}, {3.981755715673439*^9, 
   3.981755742322248*^9}, {3.9817558776338253`*^9, 3.981755897413331*^9}, {
   3.98175686097141*^9, 3.981756889293563*^9}, {3.981759030879671*^9, 
   3.981759084802044*^9}, {3.981817840073872*^9, 3.9818178799861813`*^9}, {
   3.981818046163745*^9, 3.98181806300419*^9}, {3.9818193262828293`*^9, 
   3.9818193937919483`*^9}, {3.981819444409254*^9, 3.981819501329823*^9}, {
   3.9818203110710173`*^9, 3.981820320033354*^9}, {3.981820524864704*^9, 
   3.9818205273080673`*^9}, {3.9818205701587276`*^9, 3.981820571478735*^9}, 
   3.981820647243648*^9, 
   3.981821220100877*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b6b40c1a-f46d-4589-a687-\
ee38967d22ff"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Mod", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Numerator", "[", "#", "]"}], "*", 
      RowBox[{"PowerMod", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Denominator", "[", "#", "]"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", "9"}], "]"}]}], ",", "9"}], "]"}], "&"}], "/@", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "3", ",", 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "/", "2"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"-", "2"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"-", "3"}]}], "}"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981820661962399*^9, 3.9818206841188374`*^9}, {
  3.9818207822085733`*^9, 3.981820782549304*^9}, {3.981822102683785*^9, 
