Cell[TextData[{
 "The example shows RATCONVERT can fail when precision is insufficient \
\[LongDash] the large CF term 39 in {0, 1, 2, 1, 2, 39, 2, 2} signals that \
5/11 requires far more 3-adic digits before it appears as a convergent. But \
when precision is sufficient, the algorithm is guaranteed to succeed. Here is \
why:\nThe convergence proof. Suppose u/v \[Congruent] m (mod p\:1d3a) with \
|u|, |v| \[LessEqual] \[Sqrt](p\:1d3a/2). Then u + d\[CenterDot]p\:1d3a = v\
\[CenterDot]m for some integer d, giving:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"d", "/", "v"}], "\[Minus]", 
     RowBox[{"m", "/", "p\:1d3a"}]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"u", "/", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"v", "\[CenterDot]", "p\:1d3a"}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"68f7aca4-3ea0-4b47-a8bb-bd80fd6299ac"],
 "\n\nSo d/v approximates m/p\:1d3a with error: Hence ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"d", "/", "b"}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "55e72732-ed4e-420e-8af8-e789a5b1ddcd"],
 " is an approximation to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"c", "/", "m"}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "17c6e4ee-3e57-4a20-aeef-e36fd3bb1eb6"],
 ", and, since ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", "a", "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", "b", "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], 
     RowBox[{"<=", 
      SqrtBox[
       RowBox[{"m", "/", "2"}]]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "63a35915-013f-42b4-b946-7fa5385b7601"],
 ", the error is\n\n|u/(v\[CenterDot]p\:1d3a)| \[LessEqual] \
\[Sqrt](p\:1d3a/2) / (v\[CenterDot]p\:1d3a) = \
1/(2v\[CenterDot]\[Sqrt](p\:1d3a/2)) \[LessEqual] 1/(2v\.b2)\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
     FractionBox["a", 
      RowBox[{"m", " ", "b"}]], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], "<=", 
    FractionBox[
     SqrtBox[
      RowBox[{"m", "/", "2"}]], 
     RowBox[{"m", " ", "b"}]], "<=", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     RowBox[{"2", "b", " ", 
      SqrtBox[
       RowBox[{"m", "/", "2"}]]}]], "<=", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      SuperscriptBox["b", "2"]}]]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f1a5228d-bb26-403b-a622-6e14182bf9b2"],
 "  .\n\nBy Hardy & Wright [1979] Theorem 184 (p. 153): if |p/q \[Minus] x| \
\[LessEqual] 1/(2q\.b2) then p/q is a convergent of x. Hence d/v is a \
convergent of m/p\:1d3a, and the triple (d, v, u) will be generated by the \
iteration \[LongDash] the algorithm is guaranteed to find u/v whenever it \
exists within the size bound.\nThis is what distinguishes Wang\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s algorithm from classical p-adic methods for factorization \
or GCD computation: those use the p-adic image to reconstruct integers; \
RATCONVERT uses it to reconstruct rationals, with the continued fraction \
convergent criterion providing both the termination condition and the \
uniqueness guarantee.\n\[LineSeparator]We can now appeal to Hardy & Wright \
[1979] Theorem 184 (p. 153): If\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["p", "q"], "-", "x"}], "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], "<=", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      SuperscriptBox["q", "2"]}]]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "421eaba2-7fb4-4bb0-810d-6f0519ff8ff8"],
 "\n\nthen",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{" ", 
    RowBox[{"p", "/", "q", " "}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "15d7ccab-7c91-468a-8adf-5aa6b7990ca8"],
 "is a convergent [to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["x", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "22a0bba4-08f9-4c85-8ef0-3060830b9dee"],
 "]. Hence the triple ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"d", ",", " ", "b", ",", " ", "a"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"1dce9c27-9b85-4876-bc8c-0e47334abef9"],
 ") is indeed generated by the algorithm, and so the algorithm is guaranteed \
to find a rational in the appropriate range which corresponds to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"c", " ", "mod", " ", "m"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "eb68450f-bdf8-43ac-ab15-ad86cbceafdd"],
 ", if such a value exists.\n\n[Wang, 1981] Paul S. Wang, P-adic \
Reconstruction of Rational Numbers,  M.J.T. Guy, J.H. Davenport\n[Koblitz, \
1977] N. Koblitz, P-adic Numbers, P-adic Analysis and Zeta- Functions, \
Springer-Verlag, 1977\n[Schikhof, 1984] W. Schikhof, Ultrametric Calculus : \
An introduction to p-adic analysis, Cambridge University Press, 1984"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.88478252736084*^9, {3.884783774208233*^9, 3.884783779552964*^9}, 
   3.8847838433821983`*^9, {3.884783973834618*^9, 3.88478399680987*^9}, {
   3.884788230677512*^9, 3.884788243600871*^9}, 3.8847925675016127`*^9, {
   3.884792620876239*^9, 3.8847926763586683`*^9}, {3.884793019371161*^9, 
   3.884793153284438*^9}, {3.8847932084148207`*^9, 3.884793214053976*^9}, {
   3.884793252051655*^9, 3.8847933347625227`*^9}, 3.884793403549611*^9, {
   3.884793572818577*^9, 3.884793591679605*^9}, {3.884794776270637*^9, 
   3.884794877804718*^9}, {3.8847950075623426`*^9, 3.884795120400334*^9}, {
   3.884795227511087*^9, 3.884795259548877*^9}, {3.884796304425152*^9, 
   3.884796304940444*^9}, {3.884816708202722*^9, 3.884816777617649*^9}, {
   3.88481953610236*^9, 3.884819539633766*^9}, {3.884876015311627*^9, 
   3.884876329867917*^9}, {3.8848763784942102`*^9, 3.8848764273801603`*^9}, {
   3.884876491406649*^9, 3.884876606257503*^9}, {3.8850763809134417`*^9, 
   3.885076390076433*^9}, {3.9817553238802*^9, 3.981755352955504*^9}, {
   3.9817575040884743`*^9, 3.981757505685758*^9}, {3.9817595844182873`*^9, 
   3.981759655548047*^9}, {3.981759991557022*^9, 3.981759994716223*^9}, {
   3.9818242848017883`*^9, 
   3.981824380416193*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fbcfb38e-a53e-4151-a8c3-\
5ae42bd42ed7"]
}, Open  ]]
